            <Title>Let the chord ring out</Title>
            <Text>Let the chord ring out
Mari could hardly feel herself floating on the water. Her eyes could see only the peach-colored sky and other than that, her mind could absorb no more than the deep hum of thoughts from Adno’s people.
“Do you feel our wave?” Adno asked her.
“I feel as if I am sitting in a deep metal bowl and you have struck it. All around me, everything is vibrating.”
“Good, that is a good start. When you play your guitar, you make chords, no?”
“Yes, and I can almost feel a chord in the vibrations.”
“And a rhythm, too? Not a simple repeating pattern, but can you feel pulsing?”
“Yes! I can now, and it makes the chords clearer.”
They continued for hours, Adno’s school modulating and calling out to her, her riding the wave of their minds, losing it, finding it. She became aware that the sky was dark and she began to chill. Her enhancements could no longer compensate for the coolness of the water.
“Marilon, you are so close. One last try?”
She closed her eyes, letting the thoughts of the whole school rise up through the water and warm her like a million little fingers, caresses that resolved into melodies and chords, into slow and fast grooves that overlapped and diverted and rejoined. And then it became clear, what they were telling her.
“You are one of us, we are one with you, we are one together. You follow us, we follow Adno, Adno follows you, who follow us. We feel the currents you swim in, you swim in the currents we feel.”
She had joined the school. For the first time in her life, she was part of a waveform that included every sentient being on her planet, all at once. It was vast but not chaotic, united but not uniform. She recalled flying with her mother above one of Water Eye’s many islands. This one was covered with small plants with irridescent tips. As they flew around the island, the plants wave in the wind and reflected the sun in a beautifully changing and nuanced patterns. Times a million, that was what this felt like.
She would teach Anti, and they would teach Des and Nyssa.

</Text>
