            <Title>Greetings</Title>
            <Text>Greetings
Earth
March 23, 2082
Raefe had woken before dawn. Somewhere, it was daylight and people were awake. He reached out and searched for their waveforms. He felt them swimming by in the thousands, small silvery lights in the dark. And then he he saw a brighter glow, another empath, one of trained band. He reached out to him and now they resonated. They moved together and found a third, a fourth, and their wave began to grow.
Within an hour, they had built a wave that circled the globe. Countless minds touching each other, feeling their common bond, understanding the task they faced. They were ready.
Des had hacked into the world’s vid and voice nets. Whatever Raefe chose to communicate as speech within the waveform, would also be broadcast on the world’s nets.
“People of the world,” Raefe said. “I speak to you today as a citizen of Everywhere. We have much to discuss, so I ask your patience. How you respond to what you are about to hear will determine the future of the human race. I have some shocking things to tell you, and some very hopeful news.”
“It’s no secret that the world’s largest corporations have increasingly taken over the running of the world. They use every crisis to force governments to give them more power. They use that power to benefit their owners, even when that harms the rest of us.
“What they have kept secret is that 13 of the world’s most powerful corpos have banded together and have a plan to take over the world. We have posted the documents that prove this on servers around the world and you can read them. What they say is that this secret cabal wants to build underground cities for themselves and perhaps a few million followers, take their money and resources and disappear underground, and then wait until the rest of us have destroyed ourselves fighting over the shrinking supply of food and water to come above ground and reclaim the Earth for themselves.”
He gave them some time to look up the docs and then continued explaining how this would take many generations. The documents discussed the long life treatments the super rich would give themselves, but he had decided not to dwell on that for now. There were more immediate threats to deal with.
“But as has been their habit, the super rich got greedy,” he continued. “They didn’t want to wait a hundred generations. So they planned a world-wide computer virus that would send us back to the world of more than 100 years ago, before we had computers and networks. Unprepared, we would be thrown into chaos. The fragility of our world, under constant climate disaster, our social fabric strained beyond breaking by billions of refugees, our governments no longer able to even pretend to serve us, this very fragility is what they cynically sought to leverage. But they will not succeed.”
“Just before our broadcast, citizens of Everywhere were able to penetrate this net attack and disassemble it. This cabal, led by Billy Warren, Ken Robertson and a dozen other corpos, has been thwarted.”
“Fellow humans, for the first time this century, we have averted a major disaster that could have led to our extinction. Both nature and the corpos will continue to threaten us. But we have learned more than just how to disarm massive computer attacks. We have learned how to connect.”
“Many of you know that I am an empath and for decades have been working to connect many other people with each other. When we can fully sense our fellow humans, we can create a level of trust between us that is fully capable of withstanding the stresses and strains the world puts upon us. We can work out our conflicts with full confidence that we are not being lied to or manipulated.”
“Recently, we have discovered that this ability can go far beyond the one to one interactions that I learned as a young man. As a species, we live as individuals, in small groups, in larger groups, and in the herds we call communities, tribes and nations. And it turns out, we can learn to think at those levels because we can connect into a single, complex wave, all of us, all at once.
“Right now, millions of people around the world are doing exactly that, reaching out to you. You will not lose your sense of self, your individual will, or any other such thing. You will be you, standing in a chorus of billions, humming joyfully as you see fully for the first time that your fellow humans really do want the same kind of things that you do, regardless of how different they might appear. That though we may occasionally threaten each other, we have gotten this far because, deep in our cells, we do know how to live together. No one is in charge, no one is giving orders. And you can leave the wave at will. You can sing your own notes too, if you want to alter the tune. This is not about conforming, it is about informing. So as you feel those first thoughts, reach back out to them and welcome them.”
He saw Lina across the room, her face beaming. She had let herself be swept off of that drowning beach so many years ago, not really knowing what was happening, just for this moment. He could feel the world vibrating between the many other Earths that existed on other timelines. And now he understood that the energy of that vibration was being organized and modulated by the waveform of his fellow humans, up to their chins in the mud of the swamp of greed and fear they had unintentionally built for themselves. Now, with full intention, they felt themselves ever so slowly rising up out of that swamp, into the brightness of day. A brightness that was now Everywhere.
</Text>
