            <Title>The best laid plans</Title>
            <Text>The best laid plans

Billy Warren could hardly contain his anger.
“Ken, I’m just beside myself here. I’ve put a lot of faith in you. You’ve got that whole Brightstar organization and I ask one favor of you guys and you can’t deliver. Compared to what I’ve offered you, this was nothing. And I got exactly that — nothing — for the asking.”
“I can’t tell you how sorry I am, Billy. We had him all boxed in, we had a man on the scene, in the room. He had already snuck in previously and painted the wall with a UV coating so the sniper couldn’t get confused. He had him lined up. He says the guy moved at the last second, like he knew it was coming. And then they were gone. Those Urban Gypsies are good at hiding in their territory.”
Warren could hear Hank in his ear.
“They’ll be moving Raefe. I’ve got good intel that he’s headed out. Maybe to Liverpool. Make him work this out, Billy.”
“I’ve to sources, too, Ken. And mine say he won’t be in Newcastle much longer. Maybe Liverpool?”
“That might make sense. He could get a ferry their to Ireland. Although I’d put my money on Holland — they’re allies, after all.”
“I’m expecting at least that you take the Liverpool lead seriously. If you want to cover more bases, much appreciated. I understand he’s resourceful. But we need to find him and take him off the board. Keep me posted.”
Robertson didn’t like taking orders. But who did?</Text>
