            <Title>Not so fast</Title>
            <Text>Not so fast
Dadaab
March 22, 2082

Des had become the tactical commander of Everywhere. His links to people and computers gave him an immense field of knowledge about the continually evolving situation. For now, Adno’s school backed him up, sorting through the data and evaluating threats around the globe. Today was the day when it would all go down.
“You are good leader of school,” Adno said.
“I thought you were the leader,” Des replied.
“Oh yes, of my school. You will see in time that a real school has no leader, or it has leaders everywhere. That is its strength. I meant leader of your school, the humans.”
“God, I hope not.”
“You are funny person for a human. Tomorrow you will see what I mean. Today, we have good news.”
“Bring it on.”
“We have confirmed that our friend on the council has done his part. Some of Earth’s grid will shut down, I’m sure, because the corpos don’t need our tech to shut everything down. But it will remain a coherent world-wide system, your Net. You will not be thrust into the cold deeps.”
“Excellent. Dad has absorbed your lessons. I feel very good that he will be able to link up with millions of empaths around the world. And that they will be able to sustain a waveform for long enough for the message to get out.”
“What about the corpos?”
“They’re all headed to their mouse holes. We’ve discovered where they are and we can deal with them later.”
“You are right to do that. They are the past. You are the future — keep your mind on that.”</Text>
